  "body": "When resolving imports, Buidler uses node's `require.resolve` function. Its resolution algorithm normally excludes globally installed libraries and applications. This leads to `@nomiclabs/buidler/console.sol` not being found when using a global installation of Buidler.\r\n\r\nOne way we can fix this is to add a special case for `@nomiclabs/buidler`. We should consider other alternatives though.",
